    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="930"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss
                        target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 306</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Special Adviser to the United States
                        Delegation</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BPW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bonsal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Head of the Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_JUA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-16">July 16,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="references">
                    <head>Re:</head>
                    <item>Message from <persName corresp="#p_AWD1">Dennis Allen</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_AWD1">Dennis Allen</persName> telephoned at 10:35 a.m. to
                    say that he had just had a call from <persName corresp="#p_LRDLTG1">la
                        Tournelle</persName> who stated that at last night’s <persName
                        corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_MVM1"
                        >Molotov</persName>
                    <pb facs="1415" n="1389" xml:id="pg_1389"/> dinner<note n="1" xml:id="d930fn1"
                        >See telegram <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 626, July 16, <ref
                            target="#pg_1394">p. 1394</ref>.</note> it was suggested that a meeting
                    might be held this afternoon between the two Chairmen (<persName
                        corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MVM1"
                        >Molotov</persName>) and the French to review the documents which have so
                    far been produced and to see where the Conference stands.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> has asked <persName corresp="#p_AWD1"
                        >Allen</persName> to let you know of this suggestion and to find out your
                    views. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> believes that the meeting in
                    practice might be useful. If the question of U.S. participation in such a
                    meeting is raised, <persName corresp="#p_AWD1">Allen</persName> believes that
                    the Russians will probably insist on the presence of the Chinese communists, and
                    we would thus have a five-power gathering.</p>
                <p>I told <persName corresp="#p_AWD1">Allen</persName> that we would let him have
                    your views as soon as possible.<note n="2" xml:id="d930fn2">Handwritten
                        notations on the source text indicated that Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> had “no objection” to holding the
                        meeting between the two Chairmen and the French and that <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> agreed with <persName
                            corresp="#p_AWD1">Dennis Allen</persName>’s belief that the Russians
                        would probably insist on a Chinese Communist presence which would mean a
                        five-power gathering. An additional handwritten notation indicates that
                            <persName corresp="#p_AWD1">Allen</persName> was advised of the
                        Ambassador’s notations.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
